<% layout('layouts/boilerplate') -%>
<section class="legal-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
      <p class="muted">Committed to an inclusive web</p>
      <p class="lead">We are committed to making our website accessible to everyone, including people with disabilities. This statement outlines our accessibility efforts and how you can get help.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="legal-content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="legal-nav">
      <h4>Legal Documents</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/terms-of-service">Terms of Service</a></li>
        <li><a href="/cookies-policy">Cookies Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/accessibility" class="active">Accessibility</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="accessibility-features">
      <div class="accessibility-feature">
        <div class="icon">⌨️</div>
        <div class="content">
          <h5>Keyboard Navigation</h5>
          <p>Full keyboard accessibility for all interactive elements</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accessibility-feature">
        <div class="icon">🔍</div>
        <div class="content">
          <h5>Screen Reader Support</h5>
          <p>Semantic HTML and ARIA labels for assistive technologies</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accessibility-feature">
        <div class="icon">🎨</div>
        <div class="content">
          <h5>High Contrast</h5>
          <p>Sufficient color contrast ratios for better readability</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accessibility-feature">
        <div class="icon">📱</div>
        <div class="content">
          <h5>Responsive Design</h5>
          <p>Works across all devices and screen sizes</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accessibility-feature">
        <div class="icon">🔤</div>
        <div class="content">
          <h5>Readable Fonts</h5>
          <p>Clear, legible typography optimized for readability</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="accessibility-feature">
        <div class="icon">🎯</div>
        <div class="content">
          <h5>Focus Indicators</h5>
          <p>Clear visual focus indicators for keyboard users</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <article>
      <h2>1. Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
      <p>Asparsh is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We continually improve the user experience for everyone and apply relevant accessibility standards to achieve these goals.</p>

      <h3>Accessibility Standards</h3>
      <p>We aim to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities and also make web content more usable for everyone.</p>

      <h2>2. Accessibility Features</h2>
      
      <h3>Navigation and Structure</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Logical Heading Structure:</strong> Proper use of H1-H6 headings for document structure</li>
        <li><strong>Skip Links:</strong> "Skip to main content" links for keyboard users</li>
        <li><strong>Consistent Navigation:</strong> Predictable navigation patterns across all pages</li>
        <li><strong>Breadcrumbs:</strong> Clear page location indicators where applicable</li>
        <li><strong>Site Map:</strong> Comprehensive site structure for easy navigation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Visual Design</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Color Contrast:</strong> Minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text, 3:1 for large text</li>
        <li><strong>Color Independence:</strong> Information not conveyed by color alone</li>
        <li><strong>Scalable Text:</strong> Text can be enlarged up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Layouts adapt to different screen sizes and orientations</li>
        <li><strong>Focus Indicators:</strong> Clear visual indicators for keyboard focus</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Keyboard Accessibility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tab Navigation:</strong> All interactive elements accessible via Tab key</li>
        <li><strong>Logical Tab Order:</strong> Tab sequence follows visual layout</li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard Shortcuts:</strong> Standard keyboard shortcuts where applicable</li>
        <li><strong>No Keyboard Traps:</strong> Users can navigate away from any element</li>
        <li><strong>Enter/Space Activation:</strong> Buttons and links work with Enter and Space keys</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Screen Reader Support</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Proper use of HTML elements for their intended purpose</li>
        <li><strong>ARIA Labels:</strong> Descriptive labels for complex interface elements</li>
        <li><strong>Alt Text:</strong> Descriptive alternative text for all meaningful images</li>
        <li><strong>Form Labels:</strong> Clear, descriptive labels for all form inputs</li>
        <li><strong>Status Updates:</strong> Screen reader announcements for dynamic content changes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Multimedia Accessibility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Video Captions:</strong> Closed captions for all video content</li>
        <li><strong>Audio Descriptions:</strong> Descriptive audio for visual content where necessary</li>
        <li><strong>Transcript Availability:</strong> Text transcripts for audio and video content</li>
        <li><strong>Media Controls:</strong> Accessible play, pause, and volume controls</li>
        <li><strong>Auto-play Settings:</strong> No auto-playing media with sound</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Assistive Technology Compatibility</h2>
      <p>Our website is designed to work with a variety of assistive technologies:</p>

      <h3>Screen Readers</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>JAWS:</strong> Job Access With Speech for Windows</li>
        <li><strong>NVDA:</strong> NonVisual Desktop Access for Windows</li>
        <li><strong>VoiceOver:</strong> Built-in screen reader for macOS and iOS</li>
        <li><strong>TalkBack:</strong> Android's built-in screen reader</li>
        <li><strong>ORCA:</strong> Screen reader for Linux systems</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Other Assistive Technologies</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Voice Recognition Software:</strong> Dragon NaturallySpeaking and similar tools</li>
        <li><strong>Switch Navigation:</strong> Single-switch and scanning interfaces</li>
        <li><strong>Eye-tracking Systems:</strong> Eye-gaze communication devices</li>
        <li><strong>Magnification Software:</strong> ZoomText and other screen magnifiers</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Browser and Device Support</h2>
      <p>Our website is tested and optimized for accessibility across multiple platforms:</p>

      <h3>Supported Browsers</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Google Chrome (current and previous major version)</li>
        <li>Mozilla Firefox (current and previous major version)</li>
        <li>Safari (current and previous major version)</li>
        <li>Microsoft Edge (current and previous major version)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Mobile Accessibility</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>iOS devices with VoiceOver support</li>
        <li>Android devices with TalkBack support</li>
        <li>Touch screen accessibility features</li>
        <li>Voice control compatibility</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Known Limitations</h2>
      <p>While we strive for full accessibility, some limitations may exist:</p>

      <h3>Third-Party Content</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Some embedded content from third parties may not be fully accessible</li>
        <li>Social media widgets may have limited accessibility features</li>
        <li>PDF documents may require additional accessibility improvements</li>
        <li>External payment processing forms are governed by third-party accessibility policies</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Legacy Content</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Older content may not meet current accessibility standards</li>
        <li>We are continuously working to update and improve legacy content</li>
        <li>Priority is given to the most frequently accessed content</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Ongoing Efforts</h2>
      <p>Accessibility is an ongoing commitment. Our efforts include:</p>

      <h3>Regular Testing</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Automated accessibility testing integrated into our development process</li>
        <li>Manual testing with assistive technologies</li>
        <li>User testing with people who have disabilities</li>
        <li>Regular accessibility audits by third-party experts</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Staff Training</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Regular accessibility training for all team members</li>
        <li>Design and development guidelines that prioritize accessibility</li>
        <li>Accessibility considerations in all project planning</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Continuous Improvement</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Regular review and updates of accessibility features</li>
        <li>Implementation of new accessibility technologies as they become available</li>
        <li>Response to user feedback and accessibility concerns</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. How to Use Accessibility Features</h2>
      
      <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tab:</strong> Move forward through interactive elements</li>
        <li><strong>Shift + Tab:</strong> Move backward through interactive elements</li>
        <li><strong>Enter:</strong> Activate links and buttons</li>
        <li><strong>Space:</strong> Activate buttons and toggle controls</li>
        <li><strong>Arrow Keys:</strong> Navigate within menus and form controls</li>
        <li><strong>Escape:</strong> Close modal dialogs and dropdown menus</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Browser Accessibility Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Zoom:</strong> Use Ctrl/Cmd + Plus/Minus to adjust text size</li>
        <li><strong>High Contrast:</strong> Enable in browser settings or operating system</li>
        <li><strong>Reader Mode:</strong> Available in most modern browsers</li>
        <li><strong>Voice Commands:</strong> Use browser voice control features</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Feedback and Support</h2>
      <p>Your feedback helps us improve accessibility. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please let us know:</p>

      <div class="contact-info">
        <h4>Accessibility Contact Information</h4>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= process.env.ADMIN_EMAIL || 'accessibility@asparsh.com' %>"><%= process.env.ADMIN_EMAIL || 'accessibility@asparsh.com' %></a></p>
        <p><strong>Subject Line:</strong> "Accessibility Feedback" or "Accessibility Issue"</p>
        <p><strong>Phone:</strong> [Your Phone Number] (Voice/TTY)</p>
        <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We aim to respond within 1 business day</p>
      </div>

      <h3>When Contacting Us, Please Include:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>The specific page or feature you're having trouble with</li>
        <li>The assistive technology you're using (if applicable)</li>
        <li>Your browser and operating system</li>
        <li>A description of the accessibility barrier you encountered</li>
        <li>Any suggestions you have for improvement</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Alternative Access Methods</h2>
      <p>If you cannot access content on our website, we can provide information in alternative formats:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Large print versions of documents</li>
        <li>Audio recordings of written content</li>
        <li>Plain text versions of complex documents</li>
        <li>Phone-based customer service for online services</li>
        <li>In-person assistance when possible</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>10. Legal Compliance</h2>
      <p>We strive to comply with applicable accessibility laws and standards, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</li>
        <li>Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act</li>
        <li>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</li>
        <li>European Accessibility Act</li>
        <li>Other applicable local and international accessibility standards</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="last-updated">
        <p>This accessibility statement was last updated on <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %>. We review and update this statement regularly to reflect our current accessibility efforts.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
